nalysis remains valid when the cyclic order is unknown.\nWe then provide a polynomial-time approximation scheme that gives a\n$(1+\\epsilon)$-optimal solution for this more general, NP-hard problem.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 24 Sep 2013 04:14:16 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 20 Jan 2014 12:57:48 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 21 Jan 2014 04:37:36 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Thu, 4 Sep 2014 22:17:47 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Sun, 14 Sep 2014 03:33:31 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-09-16"}
